leAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "romain-alétru-45047b74", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAA-7M7wBwQpccd0PjfWLlgYvpUDj3v0zJFE", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACjGKaABhGhcmzajeUTwrCpmnYbTAgCV-H8", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/first_name": "Sarocha", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/follower_count": "10", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "F&B Manager at the Siam", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Ditbanchong", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEggavVzwrP4g/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1724897295378?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=2zL2PDUWQ1GslTVJ5vAVc8WMEivwPRMaSH8tn5rKDhU", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "sarocha-ditbanchong-b94118171", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAACjGKaABhGhcmzajeUTwrCpmnYbTAgCV-H8", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQGmwM6yghC6EQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/B56ZaozcgmHUAo-/0/1746588781186?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=NSDpN1mQj50Mg0FUN6-xqeTvJ6qCYnrqpFXnRZE_Vnw", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQGmwM6yghC6EQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/B56ZaozcgmHUAo-/0/1746588781186?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=NSDpN1mQj50Mg0FUN6-xqeTvJ6qCYnrqpFXnRZE_Vnw", "publicIdentifier": "syahreza-ishwara-12266027", "recommendations/0/context": "Syahreza worked with Leticia on the same team", "recommendations/0/date": "December 26, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "I am pleased to provide my highest recommendation for Leticia, whom I have known for many years during our time working together at Anantara – Minor Hotels. Throughout my tenure as General Manager of Anantara Chiang Mai, Pre-opening General Manager of Anantara Ubud, Bali, and General Manager of the ultra-luxury Anantara Koh Yao Yai in Thailand, Leticia consistently stood out as an exceptional professional and an invaluable partner.\nLeticia served as our Global Sales Leader for Spain, France, and Italy, and her performance was truly remarkable. After every property visit, she delivered an impressive volume of high-quality FIT and group leads — more than any Global Sales representative I have worked with in my career. Her deep market knowledge, strategic approach, and ability to immediately translate insights into business opportunities made a significant contribution to the commercial success of all three properties.\nWhat sets Leticia apart is her passion, work ethic, and unmatched dedication. Whether traveling, on vacation, or even during maternity leave, she remained proactive, responsive, and fully committed to supporting the hotels. Her level of professionalism is rare and deeply admirable.\nBeyond her operational excellence, Leticia is also a wonderful collaborator. She is an attentive listener, solution-oriented, and consistently demonstrates kindness, respect, and empathy. She approaches challenges with calm confidence and always brings constructive, well-considered solutions.\nLeticia is, without doubt, the best Sales Leader I have ever worked with. Any organization would be incredibly fortunate to have her, and I wholeheartedly endorse her for any senior leadership or commercial role she chooses to pursue.", "recommendations/0/name": "Leticia De Andrés", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Global Director of Sales Spain , France ,Portugal & Italy", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/leticia-de-andrés-5739171b/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAQ6n2cBAiUc7WfGlGnEYc49lQLUHdQLq-E", "recommendations/1/context": "Syahreza managed Arim directly", "recommendations/1/date": "July 25, 2025", "recommendations/1/description": "I had the pleasure of working closely with Pak Harimbawo Sukarma during the pre-opening phase of Anantara Ubud Bali Resort. He was the very first executive I hired for the project, and from the beginning, he demonstrated calm confidence and consistent professionalism. His commitment was evident early on, he supported me in meeting with the local village heads in Payangan even before his official start date, reflecting both his dedication and flexibility.\n\nPre-openings are dynamic environments with fast-paced one moment and slow the next, often testing the resilience and adaptability of even the most seasoned leaders. Yet Pak Harimbawo navigated every challenge with clarity, poise, and a proactive mindset. From liaising with local villagers and government agencies to working with contractors, overseeing the pre-opening setup plan, and ensuring alignment with the brand’s standards, he remained deeply involved and solution-oriented. His strong background in human resources and clear understanding of luxury hospitality were evident in every decision and interaction.\n\nPak Harimbawo leads with a grounded presence. He is a thoughtful listener who balances empathy with a firm adherence to policies and regulations. Always approachable and collaborative, he earns the respect of colleagues and team members alike through his integrity and professionalism. His leadership brought structure, momentum, and a sense of purpose that helped guide the team through critical phases of the project.\n\nWorking with Pak Harimbawo was both an honour and a valuable learning experience. I am confident that any organization or team under his leadership will benefit immensely from his expertise, dedication, and steady guidance.\n\nSyahreza Ishwara", "recommendations/1/name": "Arim Sukarma", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Aviation Enthusiast | Area Manager | People-oriented Leader | Passionate Hotelier | Pre-opening Specialist", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arimsukarma/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAM8T1IBE4sXW9Vq3HKrlV6mgaD8afCo-m4", "recommendations/2/context": "Syahreza managed Rachmat directly", "recommendations/2/date": "May 7, 2013", "recommendations/2/description": "Rachmat is a hard working, innovative and highly commited towards his responsibilities. He treated his staffs well and he showed a strong leadership when he managed Basilico.", "recommendations/2/name": "Rachmat N.", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Director Of Food And Beverage at Marriott International", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rachmat-n-b7408220/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAARIHAgBZRyHxnEExuiQMYSI0C_HrQIQD40", "recommendations/3/context": "Syahreza managed Alexandre directly", "recommendations/3/date": "July 28, 2011", "recommendations/3/description": "Alexandre is unconventional, down to earh and extremerly flexible which is a succes formula in the hospitality industry. He tooks ownership to achieve his goals. Gave 110% dedications towards his responsibilites, a good example of an excelent trainer, very good motivator towards his subordinates and very hands on with the operations. Very strong communication skills and computer program which made him a good Director of Restaurant and Bar back at the Regent Singapore", "recommendations/3/name": "Alexandre Peghoux", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "HR Operations & Talent | Corporate HR | Structured HR Processes", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexandre-peghoux/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASJanIBYAxvnnZ7OavrkByIFpwUPbPWCVY", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Kattaleeya reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "July 30, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "It was a privilege to work with Mr. Reza Ishwara, a leader who truly stands out in every way. During our time working together, I witnessed firsthand his exceptional leadership skills, initiative, and deep commitment to operational excellence. Reza is someone who leads from the front, always taking a hands-on approach and ensuring every detail is thoughtfully managed.\n\nHe has an outstanding ability to connect with his team, earn their trust, and empower them to do their best work. His clear vision, strong values, and consistent actions set a powerful example for those around him. He doesn’t just manage people, he inspires them.\n\nWhat I especially appreciated about working with Reza was his decisiveness. He takes initiative, drives results, and fosters a culture of accountability and growth.\nI learned so much under his leadership, and I truly miss working with someone of his caliber.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Kattaleeya S.", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Director of Spa & Wellness at JW Marriott Phuket Resort and Spa: Thailand Spa Council - Representing and leading the council in Thailand", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kattaleeya-s-2b7b3879/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABC4PqsBr5X8Y404Hk4Sofy9qeMWZN_IKpM", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "I Putu reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "July 29, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "I feel fortunate to have been under Mr. Reza's leadership. He is a highly futuristic yet meticulously detailed individual in almost every aspect of hotel operations. As a senior engineer, I sometimes felt quite experienced. However, I quickly realized that there were many other aspects I could develop under Mr. Reza's leadership. I find beneficial is his patience in guiding me to not only good in engineering but almost all aspects of hotel operations, understanding brand standards, the company's vision and mission, memorizing by hearth, and implementing them. We were taught a very high commitment to service and product quality, accuracy and focus on business goals, and maintaining our identity as a specific hotel brand. What is also emphasized is profit-based sustainability and keeping up with the latest technological developments, including AI, which have a direct impact on business continuity and competition. Thank you Mr. Reza, you are simply different and the best.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "I Putu S.", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Project Manager", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/i-putu-s-1317ab4/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADUSPUBpJPnYA9C35fVv2E5wIPo4H2hKlc", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Burasakorn reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "July 27, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I feel really lucky to have had the chance to work with Khun Reza. He’s not just a great GM—he’s someone who truly cares about people and takes the time to help others grow. Working with him was one of the most valuable experiences in my career.\n\nKhun Reza is the leader who builds strong teams, supports his staff, and always looks for ways to improve the organization. He taught me so much—not just about the job itself, but about how to lead, how to handle challenges, and how to grow professionally. I’ve grown a lot because of what I learned from him.\n\nHe leads with heart, and I can feel how much he wants to see people succeed. I’m grateful I got to learn from him and be part of his team. Anyone who gets to work with Khun Reza will gain not just a great manager, but a mentor and someone who truly makes a difference.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Burasakorn Kamsuwan", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Operations Manager at Kimpton Maa-Lai Bangkok", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/burasakorn-kamsuwan-19b97bb1/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABfQfkcBO0_yUyQIpikv7rk1J0fnsimRkKY", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Røn reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "July 26, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I’ve had the profound privilege of working with Khun Reza across three distinct chapters—each one marked by transformative leadership, heartfelt mentorship, and a shared commitment to excellence. Whether through strategic assignments, operational turnarounds, or brand-defining projects, his influence has always been unmistakable.\n\nTo many of us in the younger generation of hospitality leaders, Khun Reza embodies multiple roles: a guiding father figure, an elder brother in the journey of growth, and an inspiring professional mentor who unites diverse teams into one cohesive vision.\n\nOur time together at Anantara Chiang Mai in the North and Anantara Koh Yao Yai in the South was nothing short of legacy-building. What he cultivated in these ultra-premium resorts wasn’t just operational readiness—but a foundation of discipline, culture, and emotional intelligence designed for the future of luxury hospitality. His brand delivery approach is rare: simple yet profound, elegant yet grounded—always elevating the brand without losing its soul.\n\nWhat sets Khun Reza apart is his genuine connection with people. I’ve seen him fold linen with the housekeeping team, serve food shoulder-to-shoulder with F&B, and passionately lead hands-on training sessions—not out of duty, but out of belief in people. That humility, coupled with visionary leadership, is a rare gem in today’s industry.\n\nIt has truly been an honor to work alongside someone who not only leads from the front but also touches hearts along the way.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Røn Ramirez", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Mixology Series ®", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/artofmixology/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAacP5UBeGLfGH7_M-ObIosPxUWGAXsampY", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Songklot reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "July 25, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "It was a true pleasure working under Mr. Ishwara's leadership at Rayavadee and Anantara Koh Yao Yai. He is an exceptionally knowledgeable and revenue-driven General Manager who instilled a strong sense of discipline and responsibility within the team. His encouragement for staff to strive for the best results was truly motivating. I greatly value the experience and time I spent working with him. Thank you Khun Reza!!", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Songklot Maniya", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Senior Recreation Manager | Asia Trip Manager | Product and Destination Manager | Hospitality and DMC", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/songklot-maniya-18a2ba76/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABAP93oBGObzoNoBo9ivc6NQROvzz5Rya2o", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Diky Lingga reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "July 25, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "I was very fortunate to have worked under him at The Regent Singapore.    An inspiring Leader, a good role model, a Leader who walk the talk, always lead by sample, strong in operation with amazing creativity and his eyes for detail. If there is an opportunity, I'd really like to work under his leadership.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Diky Lingga Wisnu", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Passionate Hotelier", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/diky-lingga-wisnu-47ab5325/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAVUv94B5frFSLxUTKFxu0SClR5St3pTAKQ", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "Ayu reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "July 25, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "It was a great pleasure to work under the leadership of Pak Reza. He played a key role in setting up the pre-opening team at Anantara Ubud Resort Bali Spa, carefully selecting the best talents to prepare for the resort's opening.\n\nDespite the many challenges we faced, Pak Reza successfully guided and motivated the entire team, making us feel confident and well-supported under his leadership. \n\nHis approach to training, leading by example, building trust, and helping us grow in confidence, truly reflects his exceptional leadership style.\n\nHe consistently pushed us to reach our full potential, which is one of the qualities I admired most about him. Pak Reza is not only an inspiring leader but also a mentor who genuinely motivated me to become a better version of myself. His emphasis on listening skill and attention to detail continues to leave a lasting impression on me.", "recommendationsReceived/6/name": "Ayu Sri Ekayuni", "recommendationsReceived/6/subtitle": "Director of Revenue Hongkong and Bali", "recommendationsReceived/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ayu-sri-ekayuni-72a66742/", "recommendationsReceived/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAj_AVIBxWzKN-bFeiPk1eWToBqHO-Lml78", "recommendationsReceived/7/context": "Arim reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/7/date": "July 25, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/7/description": "It was a true privilege to work under the leadership of Pak Syahreza Ishwara during the pre-opening phase of Anantara Ubud Bali Resort. As the first General Manager of the property, he set the tone for excellence, resilience, and integrity from day one. I was honored to be the second person hired, and from the very beginning, I witnessed his unwavering commitment to building a strong foundation for the resort and its team.\n\nPak Reza is a resilient and dynamic leader who leads from the front. He is not only visible and approachable to all levels of staff but also deeply invested in their growth. His leadership style balances toughness with thoughtfulness; he sets high expectations, yet always provides the support and guidance needed to meet them. He knows when to push for results and when to celebrate achievements, embodying the philosophy of working hard and playing hard.\n\nThroughout the many challenges we faced during the pre-opening period, Pak Reza stood by us with unwavering support. He nurtured a culture of attention to detail, accountability, and continuous learning. Under his guidance, we became more knowledgeable, confident, and aligned with the brand’s standards and vision.\n\nHis ability to inspire, mentor, and lead with clarity and purpose made a lasting impact on my professional journey. I am grateful for the opportunity to have worked with him and would wholeheartedly recommend him to any organization seeking a transformative and empowering leader.", "recommendationsReceived/7/name": "Arim Sukarma", "recommendationsReceived/7/subtitle": "Aviation Enthusiast | Area Manager | People-oriented Leader | Passionate Hotelier | Pre-opening Specialist", "recommendationsReceived/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arimsukarma/", "recommendationsReceived/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAM8T1IBE4sXW9Vq3HKrlV6mgaD8afCo-m4", "recommendationsReceived/8/context": "Nyoman reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/8/date": "July 25, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/8/description": "I had the opportunity to work closely with Pak Reza during the pre-opening of Anantara Ubud Bali Resort, and I truly appreciate the level of commitment and leadership he brought to the project.\n\nNavigating a pre-opening is never easy, especially with shifting timelines and high expectations but Pak Reza remained steady, focused, and deeply involved in every aspect of the operation. He was always updated on OS&E and POB progress, and his attention to detail ensured that nothing was overlooked. His strong grasp of luxury hospitality was evident in every decision made, and it set a clear tone for the standards expected.\n\nSyahreza leads with a clear vision and high standards, and it’s reflected in how he sets the pace for the team. He doesn’t just manage but he’s present, engaged, and leads by example. Working with him was a valuable experience, and I’m grateful to have been part of a project under his leadership.\n\nAnyone working with Pak Reza will find themselves challenged, supported, and pushed to bring their best to the table.", "recommendationsReceived/8/name": "Nyoman Sunarsih", "recommendationsReceived/8/subtitle": "Financial Controller | Finance Advisor | Supporting Restaurant Business with Internal Control & Reporting | Finance Advisor Property Business | Manage Own Property For Rent | Currently a Stay-at-Home Mom", "recommendationsReceived/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nyoman-sunarsih-432241253/", "recommendationsReceived/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAD6BVSYBUhTJTDmWroRQniE_FwsbvcOMPL0", "recommendationsReceived/9/context": "James reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/9/date": "July 24, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/9/description": "I had the pleasure of working under Mr. Reza during my time at Anantara Ubud Bali Resort, where he served as General Manager. From day one, his leadership set the tone for a culture of excellence, professionalism, and genuine hospitality.\n\nWhat stood out most was Mr. Reza’s ability to lead with both strategic vision and personal integrity. His vision inspired me to relocate across the globe, and from our first conversation to our final day working together, I remained confident that it was the right decision. He brought departments together effortlessly, encouraged collaboration, and consistently led by example—working alongside us rather than dictating from above, whether the focus was on team development or broader operational strategy.\n\nOn a personal level, Mr. Reza was both a mentor and a motivator. He supported my growth as a chef, encouraged creativity and innovation, and instilled a deep sense of pride in delivering excellence. His guidance had a lasting impact on me, both professionally and personally.\n\nAny hotel or hospitality group would be fortunate to have Mr. Reza at the helm. I’m truly grateful to have had the opportunity to work with and learn from such a dynamic and respected leader.", "recommendationsReceived/9/name": "James Willis ", "recommendationsReceived/9/subtitle": "Executive Head of Culinary | Michelin-Starred Restaurant | Luxury Hotels", "recommendationsReceived/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/chef-james-willis/", "recommendationsReceived/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAB57BKsBw0D9K6916HsPYQmJJf7ztIH-BkA", "recommendationsReceived/10/context": "Prabhash reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/10/date": "July 24, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/10/description": "I had the privilege of working with Mr. Reza, one of the most dynamic and forward-thinking General Manage , His commitment to business growth and innovation in food and beverage operations is truly inspiring. Always hands-on, Mr. Reza leads from the front—whether it’s launching new concepts, driving operational excellence, or supporting his team through every challenge.\n\nWhat sets him apart is his constant drive for improvement and his genuine passion for developing people. His leadership style fosters a strong, motivated team, and his strategic mindset consistently delivers results.\n\nWorking with Mr. Reza has been a great learning experience, and I’m confident he will continue to make a significant impact wherever he goes.\n\nPrabhash Prabhakaran ", "recommendationsReceived/10/name": "Prabhash Prabhakaran", "recommendationsReceived/10/subtitle": "Executive Chef at Anantara Mina Al Arab Ras Al khaima", "recommendationsReceived/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/prabhash-prabhakaran-1350431b/", "recommendationsReceived/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAQZSPkBnXdkXIoHX3XYmYOvuuae5hZnsTQ", "recommendationsReceived/11/context": "Sinta reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/11/date": "July 24, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/11/description": "I had the privilege of working under Bapak Syahreza during the pre-opening of Anantara Ubud, one of the most challenging experiences in my career. As General Manager, he demonstrated focus and exceptional attention to detail and consistently led by example.\n\nEven during difficult times filled with uncertainties and countless challenges, he remained a steady presence for the team and always seeking solutions and ensuring that we always felt supported. \n\nWhile his leadership can appear tough on the outside, he is, in reality, a mentor who deeply cares about the growth and learning of his team.\n\nWhat I admire most is his ability to balance high expectations with genuine guidance, it is more like a father figure who celebrates every milestone of his team achievement. His leadership helped us to be a stronger professionals.\n\nI am truly grateful to have learned from him.", "recommendationsReceived/11/name": "Sinta Angga Dewi", "recommendationsReceived/11/subtitle": "Food and Beverage Coordinator", "recommendationsReceived/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sinta-angga-dewi-a74409113/", "recommendationsReceived/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABxb4rgBesax02IPcrhAlyxxNjpHnW2V_iA", "recommendationsReceived/12/context": "Rachmat reported directly to Syahreza", "recommendationsReceived/12/date": "May 7, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/12/description": "Mr. Syahreza Ishwara is one of the best leaders I have ever had in my professional career. He has a great ability to immediately befriend people, gain their trust, encourage them to carry on their projects /works. He is a super operational person, very hands on in every aspect. He promotes the success of his team within his organization.\n\nMr. Reza's values: He has always had a clear set of values. He believes in those, he lives by those,  he promotes those, he grows those  and he does it by example. \n\nI really miss to work with such a leader\n\nRachmat", "recommendationsReceived/12/name": "Rachmat N.", "recommendationsReceived/12/subtitle": "Director Of Food And Beverage at Marriott International", "recommendationsReceived/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rachmat-n-b7408220/", "recommendationsReceived/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAARIHAgBZRyHxnEExuiQMYSI0C_HrQIQD40", "skills/0/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/1/title