ospitality | Corporate Recruiter & Human Resources", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Yutthasetpong", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "yupa-yutthasetpong-694429126", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAB8H8pAB8dMIUktOWFITgj1nfa5q5GjZPt0", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEaGXYx_mBSlw/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1665836616468?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=Pvq72jfqmCpr37vsdFRs6olpe9PX4LIUGoigpxGpuMs", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQEaGXYx_mBSlw/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1665836616468?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=Pvq72jfqmCpr37vsdFRs6olpe9PX4LIUGoigpxGpuMs", "publicIdentifier": "renebalmer", "recommendations/0/context": "Rene was Anthony's client", "recommendations/0/date": "June 13, 2021", "recommendations/0/description": "It is not enough to have the correct customer intelligence systems. It is advisable having a partner assisting and guiding the feedback by correlating the information and make the right conclusions. \nWorking over ten years with Review Pro, I saw many people come and go. However, I am pretty fond of Anthony, which assisted our company in getting the employees interested in the customer feedback and driving the guest experience. \nHe is very approachable and very flexible in terms of going the extra miles. Indeed, he is one of my industry partners that I can count on getting good advice. ", "recommendations/0/name": "Anthony Tan", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Hospitality Vertical Lead, SEA, CSM®", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anthony-tan-ph/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHCVIcBJmDzfjECV0fNx8OJx9bY0T0oTds", "recommendations/1/context": "Younes was Rene's client", "recommendations/1/date": "March 5, 2017", "recommendations/1/description": "I worked with Younes on a number of implementations for Absolute Hotel Services with Eastin Hotels &Residences and U Hotels&Resorts as brands. Besides the fact that he made sure the programs are running smoothly, he was always ready to take my call regardless when. He is very approachable and very flexible in terms of going the extra miles. Surely, he is one of my industry partners that I would like to stay in touch with and I hope I will have the opportunity to work with Younes again.", "recommendations/1/name": "Younes Hammoumi⚡️", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Professional Certified Coach (PCC) | PMP | SAFe Practice Consultant (SPC) | Prosci Train-the-Trainer | Success Facilitator | Leader Customer Success | SaaS Strategy & Delivery", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/hammoumi/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHMeQgBQWK_ZGy97Yrjk5V4aPaW5kDiD9Q", "recommendations/2/context": "Rene was senior to Sri Gregor but didn't manage Sri Gregor directly", "recommendations/2/date": "December 18, 2011", "recommendations/2/description": "Mr. Pfaff is regarded as a professional pastry chef and was an asset to The Dome, showing particular flair for not only producing high standards in producing a la carte desserts and buffets but also for developing his team through his leadership. \n\nAt all the times he demonstrated a very professional approach and was available to meet the long hours and the demands needed for the day to day operation. All of our Restaurants were awarded by Condé Nast “Top 80 tables of the World”.\n\nHe was also involved producing for the 3* Michelin chefs at the Epicurean Masters of the World in February 2007 all the desserts, where was quite successful event. Especially our final Gala Dinner which did cost 25,000.- US $ per person.", "recommendations/2/name": "Sri Gregor Pfaff", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "⭐️The TOP Person Ambassador/ Culinary & Travel Writer/ Spiritual ॐ/ Artist/ Executive Pastry Chef/ Corporate Chef/ Maître Chocolatier/ leading mind of Karma Hospitality Consultants Blvd.", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sri-gregor-pfaff-8b542415/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMWggkBoOKviFT65yRk7RUa-4pYp7ZsBWI", "recommendations/3/context": "Rene managed Roberto directly", "recommendations/3/date": "July 25, 2010", "recommendations/3/description": "Roberto is regarded as a professional Sommelier in our group and is an asset to The Dome, showing particular flair for not only producing high standards in recommending wines, but also for developing the waiters and waitresses through his leadership. \n\nAt all the times he demonstrated a very professional approach and was available to meet the long hours and the demands needed for the day to day operation. All of our Restaurants were awarded by Condé Nast “Top 80 tables of the World” in 2005 and the Breeze Restaurant in 2007.\n\nHe was also involved of organizing and selecting the wines for the Epicurean Masters of the World in February 2007, where was quite successful event. Especially our final Gala Dinner where cost 25,000.- US $ per person.", "recommendations/3/name": "Roberto Gallotto", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Independent Wine Consultant", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/robertogallotto/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALPw08B_jsmbjoUJT2JcOhDmoKbUGxcNKk", "recommendations/4/context": "Rene was senior to Savinee but didn't manage Savinee directly", "recommendations/4/date": "March 28, 2010", "recommendations/4/description": "Savinee, did work with us under great pressure to get the Dome restaurants at State Tower Bangkok well known locally as well internationally. To go from almost nowhere to the status which the restaurant complex has now belongs to a large part to here dedicated and creative work. I am sure she will develop herself further to be a great pillar in any company. I would like to take this opportunity to wish him every success in his future endeavors.", "recommendations/4/name": "Savinee D.", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Sr. Engineering Program Manager at Google", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/savinee/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEVBfsB6REz7RYX_3IP1Mnn2wEGA1AXMCc", "recommendations/5/context": "Rene worked with Sanjog on the same team", "recommendations/5/date": "December 8, 2009", "recommendations/5/description": "I do know Sanjog over 10 years and seen him growing to the present position, this due to his dedication at work and also heading hospitality associations in Bangkok which profits from his different approaches. He always is looking for new ways to get the better out of any position he is in. Therefore I am convinced he will grow fast further in his career.", "recommendations/5/name": "Sanjog Modgil", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Hospitality Asset Management | VP Asset Management | Driving Value Creation, Profitability, Cost Optamization & Operational Excellence, Across a Global Portfolio | Marriott, Hyatt, IHG, Accor, Melia, Minor, ONYX |", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sanjogmodgil/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMVIcUBZrx99pw9ed3N3GYoswJkyQki-LE", "recommendations/6/date": "December 8, 2009", "recommendations/6/description": "I did work together with Andreas Mueller at the Amari Atrium. Andreas has contributed to the success of this operation through his commitment, attention to details and understanding of the local culture. This was the reason why the company put him in place as a GM within the Amari Group. He has proven himself again and again in different locations which shows his dedication to his work.", "recommendations/6/name": "Andreas Müller", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "Hotelier", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreas-müller-40969a4/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADQJskBGoVGzxcaH_MHt0_NN70LzGZX3go", "recommendations/7/context": "Rene was senior to Nina but didn't manage Nina directly", "recommendations/7/date": "June 27, 2009", "recommendations/7/description": "I have learned to know Nina as a very strong and dynamic person with a high level of professionalism in sales of 5* hotel industries. She has shown excellent communication and analytical skills and is very efficient in expanding a most interesting personal network. It was a pleasure working with Nina in a difficult environment but due to here flexibility and eagerness she performed well.", "recommendations/7/name": "Nina S.", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Proactive and trusted luxury hospitality Sales business owner covering Europe and UK with experienced Team based in key markets driving Sales to your Hotel, Resort, DMC .@LuxCrest | Luxury Sales Experts |", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nina-s-b1b9104/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADYw0cBd53ZFWnegrLOs0v2ogXn4fkc-Ps", "recommendations/8/context": "Rene worked with Yann but they were at different companies", "recommendations/8/date": "May 29, 2009", "recommendations/8/description": "I did work with Yann together at Lebua where he was the F&B Asst. Director looking after one of the most luxurious and demanding operations here in Asia. He assisted us with great dedication and did lead the F&B team as an great example. Due to his interest he always was looking for new ways to improve an already very detailed operation where could be done only with a top professional knowledge.  With his character he was also very appreciated and well known by our customers, where valued his assistance to detail.", "recommendations/8/name": "Yann Gouriou", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Founder - CEO @ Unicorn Hospitality | Co-Founder - COO @ Wink", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/yanng17/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAElCVEBoYbc9_Wd-6DlffCx_2s7P-2zUqc", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Sri Gregor reported directly to Rene", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "March 21, 2021", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "Mr. Rene Balmer, one of a few to overshadow others. Succeeding through knowledge on Chef stages and fare above. Mastered minds, professional throughout, comparable to a fine handmade Swiss Watch in detail.\n\nI was fortunate to work under Mr. Balmer and benefit from learning lessons, on top realizing that real leaders teach with brains and honest thoughts and stand by you with real honest character.\n\nI am always proud and thankful for those valuable experiences and moments shared.\n\n", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Sri Gregor Pfaff", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "⭐️The TOP Person Ambassador/ Culinary & Travel Writer/ Spiritual ॐ/ Artist/ Executive Pastry Chef/ Corporate Chef/ Maître Chocolatier/ leading mind of Karma Hospitality Consultants Blvd.", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sri-gregor-pfaff-8b542415/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMWggkBoOKviFT65yRk7RUa-4pYp7ZsBWI", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Rene was senior to Savinee but didn't manage Savinee directly", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "March 23, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "It was such a pleasant working with Mr.Balmer. All the journalists, both local and international, were impressed by his culinary and management skills without the need of introduction from me. He is a valuable team member that would goes beyond his responsibility to assists the rest of the team in achieving the company's goal, even though that means a longer day for him. Any additional requests from advertising production crew or journalists were provided without questions asked. In the situation where we faced an endless stress and demanding force, he remained calm and treated every team member with respect. I appreciate his assistance in making my job a lot easier and pleasant.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Savinee D.", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Sr. Engineering Program Manager at Google", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/savinee/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEVBfsB6REz7RYX_3IP1Mnn2wEGA1AXMCc", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Sanjog worked with Rene but on different teams", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "December 8, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Rene at the Amari Atrium Hotel. His culinary talent, creativity, passion, commitment, desire to grow and develop people is exemplary and in combination with his strong organizational abilities. With his stong follow up skills and financial understanding he presents himself as an excellent team player and an asset to any organaization. I wish him all the best in his future endevours.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Sanjog Modgil", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Hospitality Asset Management | VP Asset Management | Driving Value Creation, Profitability, Cost Optamization & Operational Excellence, Across a Global Portfolio | Marriott, Hyatt, IHG, Accor, Melia, Minor, ONYX |", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sanjogmodgil/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMVIcUBZrx99pw9ed3N3GYoswJkyQki-LE", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Andreas was senior to Rene but didn't manage Rene directly", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "December 7, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Rene at the Amari Atrium in Bangkok.Rene is a true proffessional in every sense and has taken the culinary side of the hotel to great heights.Apart from being an innovative Kitchen proffessional ,he has excellent leadership and administrative skills. He introduced and implemented the Hotelshell.com purchasing system and streamlined the purchasing process, saving substantial amounts on the food cost without scrificing any quality.Rene is a dedicated team player a man with the highest integrity ,and an asset to any organization .", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Andreas Müller", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Hotelier", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreas-müller-40969a4/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADQJskBGoVGzxcaH_MHt0_NN70LzGZX3go", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Yann reported directly to Rene", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "May 27, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "lebua @ State tower is a very demanding hotel and has one of the most regarded F&B operation in Asia. K. Rene has contributed to the success of this operation through his commitment, attention to details, understanding of the Thai culture and great organization skills. As we use to say in our industry you don't get respect you gain it, well K. Rene has gained mine and the one of many others for the above reasons and much more.", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Yann Gouriou", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Founder - CEO @ Unicorn Hospitality | Co-Founder - COO @ Wink", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/yanng17/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAElCVEBoYbc9_Wd-6DlffCx_2s7P-2zUqc", "skills/0/title": "Sustainable Business", "skills/1/title": "Hotel Development", "skills/2/title": "Business Strategy", "skills/3/title": "Business Development", "skills/4/title": "Branding", "skills/5/title": "Hospitality Projects", "skills/6/title": "Customer Satisfaction", "skills/7/title": "Financial Analysis", "skills/8/title": "Hotel Design", "skills/9/title": "Food Industry", "skills/10/title": "Construction Management", "skills/11/title": "Team Leadership", "skills/12/title": "Management", "skills/13/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/14/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/15/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/16/title": "Resorts", "skills/17/title": "AutoCAD", "skills/18/title": "Hotels", "skills/19/ti